[49m[38;5;10m+    196[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    197[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## General Architecture Pattern
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    198[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    199[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A healthcare care coordination assistant decomposes into ten logical stages: enrollment and granular consent, longitudinal-store initialization with cross-system reconciliation, channel entry with disclosure, input safety screening with continuous emergency screening, identity-and-context loading with care-plan reconciliation, conversation handling with care-plan-grounded responses, output safety screening with scope verification, warm handoff to the human care manager when applicable, care-team reporting with consent enforcement, and audit logging with retention discipline. The cross-cutting concerns from recipes 11.1 through 11.8 carry forward; this recipe adds five new ones (cross-system care-plan reconciliation as architectural primitive, referral-loop closure tracking as architectural primitive, transition-of-care state-machine handling, multi-clinician scope-of-practice routing, and SDOH detection-and-routing).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    200[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    201[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    202[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── ENROLLMENT + GRANULAR CONSENT ────────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    203[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    204[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Patient enrolls via institution app, payer portal,    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    205[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    care-management referral, or post-discharge intake]   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    206[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Documented consent specific to care coordination    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    207[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      with care-management-leadership and legal-counsel-  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    208[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      reviewed language                                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    209[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Bot identified as a chat tool, not a person, not a  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    210[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      care manager, not a clinician                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    211[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Scope explained: navigation, tracking, surfacing,   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    212[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      warm handoff                                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    213[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Crisis-resource information surfaced                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    214[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Privacy posture explained in plain language         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    215[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Per-source consent: patient consents to bot         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    216[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      accessing each clinical-data source individually    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    217[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Per-clinician consent: patient consents to bot      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    218[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      sharing summaries with each clinician individually  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    219[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Per-purpose consent: patient consents to specific   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    220[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      data uses (care coordination, outcome correlation,  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    221[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      quality reporting, research) individually           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    222[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Caregiver consent: where a family caregiver is the  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    223[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      active operator, caregiver authentication and       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    224[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      authorization are documented separately             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    225[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - State-specific consent variations enforced          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    226[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    227[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    228[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: signed consent record with granular consent   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    229[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    matrix; enrollment confirmation; initialization of    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    230[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    longitudinal store and care-plan reconciliation]      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    231[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    232[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    233[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
