[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    620[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    621[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    622[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A few cross-cutting design points specific to the care coordination assistant.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    623[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    624[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Cross-system care-plan reconciliation as architectural primitive.** The reconciled view is the bot's working representation, not the source of truth. Refresh on enrollment, on every meaningful event, and on a defined periodic cadence with version stamping.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    625[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    626[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Referral-loop closure tracking with state machine.** Every open referral is tracked through the lifecycle. The closure rate is a launch-gate metric.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    627[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    628[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Transition-of-care state-machine handling.** Time-windowed protocols drive the bot's engagement. The bot surfaces gaps to the care manager.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    629[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    630[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Multi-clinician scope-of-practice routing.** Routing rules are institutional-protocol-driven and reviewed by clinical leadership.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    631[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    632[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Cross-system consent-gated data access.** Consent is per-source-per-clinician-per-purpose, revocable per element, enforced operationally.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    633[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    634[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Care-manager-augmenting workflow integration.** Bi-directional integration with the care manager: assignments down, surfaces up, mutual visibility.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    635[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    636[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **SDOH detection-and-routing.** Detection language is reviewed by social-work clinical leadership; routing connects to social-work and community-navigation.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    637[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    638[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Caregiver-handling discipline.** Authenticated caregivers operating on behalf of patients are recognized and routed appropriately.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    639[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    640[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Per-cohort monitoring is non-negotiable.** Metrics vary by language, channel, condition mix, age cohort, sex, social-determinant flags, and caregiver-vs-patient operator. Per-cohort dashboards reviewed by care-management leadership, operations, compliance, and patient-experience teams.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    641[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    642[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Disaster-recovery topology.** When the EHR, the referral system, the pharmacy system, the home-health system, the care-management workforce queue, or any escalation pathway is unreachable, the bot degrades gracefully. The minimum behavior is "I'm having trouble accessing your records right now; if this is urgent please call your care manager at..." with direct routing to the human.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    643[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    644[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
